1.) how array is stored in memory - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_8-ht2AKyH4

* code is stored in memory -- separate space

* global variables are stored in memory -- separate space

* functions and its local variables are stored in stack
eg - main(), demo() , test() and the scope of their local variable can't be changes
Stack size is defined by OS and compiler and excessive use might leads to stackoverflow

* Dynamic Memory allocation is done using heap memory (not DS)
Heap is simply a free pool of memory[as large as max size of memory]
in C, C++..variables on the heap stays as long as the program runs
We need to manually clean the heap using free or delete


